    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-15T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-15T21:00:00-05:00" n="517"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d517">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.01/63: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-15T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 15, 1932—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 16—2:08 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>133. Recognition was discussed this afternoon at a meeting of the Diplomatic
                    Corps. Peru has recognized and the Nuncio, the Spanish and the Brazilian
                    Ambassadors and the Cuban, Colombian and the Portuguese Ministers have
                    recommended immediate recognition. Certain other chiefs of mission expressed
                    opinion that their deliberation and delay are justified. The Argentine said that
                    he wished to follow our lead. The French expressed himself in favor of some
                    delay. The British, the German and the Italian Chargé d’Affaires have
                    recommended that their Governments first consult with you.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BJE1">Barros Jarpa</persName>, President of the Credit
                    Mortgage Bank, apparently acting as personal representative of <persName
                        corresp="#p_DCG1">Dávila</persName>, called on me this afternoon. He spoke
                    with confidence of the strength of <persName corresp="#p_DCG1"
                    >Dávila</persName>’s position. He said that the law expropriating bank deposits
                    would be annulled and that all other foreign rights would be respected. He said
                    that <persName corresp="#p_DCG1">Dávila</persName> is opposed to the
                    introduction of socialism by violent measures and hopes to achieve his program
                    gradually by education. <persName corresp="#p_DCG1">Dávila</persName> is clearly
                    making an effort to reassure foreign governments with respect to protection of
                    foreign interests.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
